National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: Lake City, SC
Accident Number: ERA11CA002
Date & Time: 10/01/2010, 1330 EDT
Registration: N8742
Aircraft: FLEET 16B
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Abrupt maneuver
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis According to the pilot, he was back taxiing on the runway when the tailwind and runway slope allowed the airplane to gain more than normal taxi speed.
As the pilot realized the airplane was approaching the end of the runway, he began to apply brake pressure to avoid running off the end of the runway.
The airplane nosed over and came to rest inverted, substantially damaging the rudder.
A postaccident examination of the airplane revealed no mechanical malfunctions that would have precluded normal operation.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: The pilotâ„¢s improper use of the brakes while taxiing.
